<section xmlns   ="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
         xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
         xml:id  ="mds-folder"
         xml:lang="en"
         version ="5.0">
  <title>Creating and Deleting Folders</title>
  <para>
    You can create and delete folders anywhere in the Browser.
    You can delete the browser itself but this does not remove anything from the repository.
  </para>
  <section xml:id="mds-folder-01">
    <title>Create a Folders</title>
    <para>
      To create a folder:
    </para>
    <orderedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Right-click in the browser in which you want create a folder on a certain folder and select <emphasis role="strong">Create Folder...</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>create</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/manage/mds/201.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </para>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          In the <emphasis role="strong">Create Folde</emphasis> dialog enter a name (for this example, test is entered) for the folder name, and click <emphasis role="strong">OK</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>create</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/manage/mds/202.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </para>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          The new folder is created as a subfolder of the selected folder
        </para>
        <para>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>create</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/manage/mds/203.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="mds-folder-02">
    <title>Delete a Folders</title>
    <important>
      <para>
        Some of the folders especially the root folders displayed in the browser are not removable.
      </para>
      <para>
        All of them are required to let Identity Manager be operational hence; the delete option will be disabled for those folders.
      </para>
    </important>
    <para>
      To delete a folder:
    </para>
    <orderedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Right-click in the browser in which you want delete a folder on a certain folder and select <emphasis role="strong">Delete</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>create</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/manage/mds/301.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </para>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Confirm the operation in the dialog box displayed.
        </para>
        <para>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>create</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/manage/mds/302.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </para>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          The folder is deleted.
        </para>
        <para>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>create</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/manage/mds/303.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
  </section>
</section>